# Corporate Finance & Risk Assessment

## Overview
This project analyzes multi-year financial data across six industries (Finance, Manufacturing, Healthcare, Technology, Energy, Retail) to evaluate performance trends and risk indicators. Built with a MySQL star schema (dim_company, dim_date, fact_financial), it calculates revenue YoY growth, profit margins, debt-equity ratios, financial leverage, and working capital ratios. Two executive-level Power BI dashboards provide Finance and Risk overviews for strategic decision-making.

## Objective
- Analyze industry financial performance and growth trends
- Evaluate risk exposure through leverage and liquidity metrics
- Identify top-performing industries and risk outliers

## Tools Used
- **Excel** — Data cleaning and preprocessing
- **MySQL** — Star schema modeling and SQL analytics
- **Power BI** — Interactive dashboards and visualizations
- **DAX** — Calculated measures and KPIs

## Data Model
Star schema with one-to-many relationships:

- **dim_company** — Company ID and industry sector
- **dim_date** — Date hierarchy (year, quarter, month, month_name)
- **fact_financial** — Financial metrics: cash_flow, current_assets, current_liabilities, debt_equity_ratio, net_income, operating_income, return_on_assets

## Key Metrics
| Metric | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| Total Revenue | Sum of net_income by industry |
| Total Profit | Sum of operating_income |
| Profit Margin % | Profit / Revenue |
| Revenue YoY % | Year-over-year revenue growth |
| Debt-Equity Ratio | Leverage indicator |
| Financial Leverage | Liabilities / Assets |
| Working Capital Ratio | Liquidity health indicator |

## Key Insights
- Revenue shows steady growth with peak in 2024
- Finance sector leads in total revenue
- Manufacturing shows highest profit margin
- Healthcare shows higher leverage ratio (elevated risk)
- Technology maintains strong working capital position
- Retail has lower asset base compared to peers
- Energy is in moderate risk situation

## Dashboards

### Finance Executive Overview
- Revenue vs Profitability scatter plot by industry
- Revenue trend over time (2016–2024)
- Profit trend over time
- Revenue by industry (bar chart)
- Profit margin by industry (bar chart)

### Risk Overview
- Assets vs Liabilities by industry
- Financial Leverage by industry
- Working Capital Ratio by industry

## SQL Queries
All SQL scripts are in the `/sql` folder:
1. Schema creation
2. Dimension tables
3. Fact table
4. Revenue by industry
5. Revenue YoY trend
6. Profit margin analysis
7. Risk assessment (debt-equity, leverage)
8. Working capital ratio

